Package: rollio
Version: @DEB_VERSION@
Architecture: @DEB_ARCH@
Maintainer: Rollio Maintainers <rollio@localhost>
Section: video
Priority: optional
Depends: can-utils, iproute2, kmod, udev, usbutils, @SHLIBS@
Description: Rollio robotics data collection framework
 Ships controller binaries under /usr/bin and the terminal/web UI
 bundles under /usr/share/rollio. Also installs the AIRBOT Play CAN
 host setup (helper scripts under /bin, udev rules under
 /lib/udev/rules.d, and the slcan@ systemd unit under
 /lib/systemd/system) so the rollio-device-airbot-play binary works
 without a separate airbot-play-rust install. Shared-library
 Depends are derived from
 all shipped binaries except rollio-encoder (install FFmpeg/Ubuntu
 libav* packages separately if you use the encoder). Node.js is not
 listed as an apt dependency because Ubuntu's `nodejs` package lags
 the version Ink/the terminal UI need; `rollio setup` detects Node
 at runtime and points operators at https://nodejs.org/en/download
 if it is missing. The Nero hardware driver is shipped separately
 as the rollio_device_nero Python wheel.
